race.comment: BIALIATSKI (1) has plenty of ability but is a work in progress. He missed the kick by 5L at Nhill first up and came with a huge run to just miss. He's trialled satisfactorily since and John Allen is reunited in a key jockey switch. Rates well on his 0.8L defeat at Ballarat Synthetic on debut and he maps for a soft run. SINGLES MOMENT (8) jumped out well and didn't have the best of it when just missing a place at Stawell on debut. Strips fitter and he can improve into the finish with average luck in the run  PULL MY FINGER (2) led and made good improvement beaten 2.2L at Stony Creek. He's disappointed since his impressive debut and may be on the way to better things. RED FALCON (7) has the rail and is an improver to consider.
